text: Johnnies is a typical downtown Chicago breakfast and lunch place, with a couple of exceptions.  First, they make their own soup from scratch.  And second, they have fair prices.  Third, the people that work there are really nice and helpful.  I've been to Johnnie's three times now: once for breakfast and twice for lunch. The breakfast sandwich with sausage, egg and cheese on an English Muffin is perfect for carrying to work. It stays in tact and stays hot the way they wrap it up.  For lunch, I've had a Badger burger with American cheese, tons of crispy bacon along with lettuce and tomato, and it was tasty. The fries are just okay. I'd order the rings if I were you.  The other time I was there, I had beef barley soup, and it was outstanding. Great flavor, lots of beef with the barley and not too salty, either. A bowl is $8 and pretty much all you neew for lunch.  They take credit cards, too.
Food was delicious! Our order came out pretty fast and our waitress was super nice. They greeted us as soon as we walked in. Will definitely be back

Johnnys used to be a great place to dine until the ownership changed a few years back. It was a drastic change for the worst sadly as this used to be my fav place for breakfast...My last two visits were consistently poor in service and the food. First 2 steps in the door we were warned by a waitress & before being seated that whatever we ordered would take up to 40 min to be prepared. Not a great way to be greeted to dine. The menue really didn't change that I could tell. I ordered the same items I've been ordering for years. Food was undercooked, bland, slopped together, and missing basics like cheese. I asked for the cheese to be added per the menue description & they resolved the problem by returning the sandwhich with a cold slice of cheese thrown on..bacon never came out but still charged for it. Waitres was not seen or checked in post cheese incident so we sat for 15min waiting for a check that never arrived. Eventually just got up and paid at the register..what a waist for a once decent place that was established way before Randolph St. is what it is today..I don't see them lasting much longer unless there is another ownership/staff change and realisation on taking pride in the food you serve & customer service.

The place is very quaint, the décor is tasteful and fits the atmosphere. Service: They were polite and courteous. Food: Looks good and appitizing, but lacks the artistic flare on the meal. What you see is what you get. The food however is what I expected for the taste. Will recommend people to go and grab a quick bite from this place.

I love it here. Reminds me of the diner where I grew up in Ohio, affordable and the staff treats you like family. Living in Fulton River District for over 12 years, there's been a lot of changes and they're mostly all great, but I hope Johnnie's never changes or goes away.
I'll give this place one star! I ordered from uber eats and never got my second meal! They couldn't even resolve my issue! Never even got taste my DAMN FOOD.

Placed a To-go order sat for twenty minutes waiting in front of the counter only person here waiting for food, a very simple order and what do you know never gave my order to the cook. Already paid and hungry I definitely won't be ordering from here again.  Instead of apologizing and acknowledging there mistake they ignore my existence what a shame. Horrible service.

The cook Francisco is great but the service is terrible. NO one knows what's going on. The servers can't handle more than one task or table at a time. This place use to be one of my favorites but sadly not any more.

I am here almost every day at lunch. Johnnies is a rare find, reasonable prices, nothing too fancy, just good food.  I cant speak for anything except their breakfast food as thats all I've ever had here, but I highly recommend their chicken n' waffles, its not on the menu but they make it and it is great!  They also have stellar french toast and pancakes.

As a fairly regular customer, I hate to give only 2 stars but the service here has been on a decline for months now. About a month ago, it took so long for our food to come out that we were not the only customers who got up and left.  Slower paced service is understandable when the small staff seems overworked (which they often are) but it completely rubs me the wrong way when an order is sloppily brought out and presented to paying customers with no remorse. Only half of one French toast order was brought out (I know it was half since I always order it) and so I called the waitress out on it. She then put another piece of French toast on its own plate and brought that out separately. In addition, all of the sides were mixed up and cold. I asked her to take it all back and bring it out the the way it was ordered. The French toast was thrown together and the eggs that were missing cheese was brought out with unmelted cheese thrown on top.  I don't write Yelp reviews but Johnnie's used to be a prime breakfast spot. I hope they can get back to that place because as of late, they are anything but.

The food was standard breakfast and it was good-- but oh my goodness, our server was either in another dimension or just did not care to be diligent in her duties. We were seated promptly when we arrived, but we had to wait at least 10-15 mins before our server came over to greet us. Then, we waited another 10 mins to order. The food came in a decent amount of time-- and we ate and enjoyed. However, we asked for a check TWICE from another waitress (we asked her to send our waitress over since we were not seeing her, and this is not a large restaurant... so, clearly she was doing something in the kitchen, or probably smoking a cigarette out back). We waited for almost 30 MINUTES, and we didn't even end up getting a check. We had to go up to the cash register where the bus boy ended up cashing us out. NO TIP, and NOT RETURNING. I can get an identical meal elsewhere for about the same price ($18 total for 2 people) and I know there are better, harder workers out there.

We ended up at Johnnie's after realizing that our preferred brunch spot didn't open for another hour.  After some serious power shopping at a warehouse sale, we were hungry but not patient, so we kept walking and came across Johnnie's. The first thing I noticed when we walked in was the sign by the register encouraging customers to write a positive Yelp review in exchange for a yogurt parfait.  It reminded me of this one episode of Maury, where a teenage girl said she had sex for a cheeseburger and a soda.  Have some standards, people! Service was OK.  Food was OK.  This kind of ordinary diner is not what you'd expect tucked around the corner from the noteworthy restaurants on Randolph.  I had an omelet with spinach, feta, and gyro meat.  There wasn't nearly enough feta, the dish was under-seasoned, and the eggs were over-cooked. The interior of the diner, and the average rating of Johnnie's, gave me initial high hopes that we stumbled upon a cheap breakfast spot with fantastic food.   Meh.

Johnnie's had been my go to for the last 3 years I've been in the west loop. The last couple months the service has not been there. The food has taken in excess of 30 minutes to come out of the kitchen while the restaurant is steadily busy, but not packed. Sometimes your waiter comes by within an acceptable amount of time to give you a menu/take an order and sometimes you're sitting there for 10 minutes until your waiter stops by for the first time. I've given Johnnie's more than a couple second chances as everyone has an off day, but it's turned into a recurring theme here now. After my most recent visit, I was informed the excessive wait for the food to come out was due to Uber Eats. Maybe the way to go with Johnnie's is delivery and not dine in?
Service is painfully bad and slow. Waiting 25 minutes for scrambled eggs and pancakes---really? I used to love this place. Will be my last time here I think.
Kim and Sophia provided great service today!!! The food is wonderful. The atmosphere is cozy and home like. This is a place of home away from home.

My new favorite neighborhood breakfast and lunch spot!! Staff is so friendly, food is on point. Exactly what you want when you need you need a pancake/egg/bacon fix. Turkey club is great too and fries are nice and crispy. Been here twice in the last week and will be here many more times to come. The staff treats you like family .

2.5 stars I'm not going to tell you where we were before we dined here. Because this particular warehouse sale should be kept under wraps. Let's just say 3 gals shopped 'til we dropped and were looking for a place that would seat us immediately and where we could rest our feet. It's a diner. It was actually a nicer looking diner than I expected.  The menu is huge--the usual suspects--pancakes, omelets, French toast, skillets, sandwiches, burgers.  And breakfast served all day.  I opted for an egg white omelet--spinach, tomato and bacon.  And sub fruit for the potatoes.   My order was pretty much wrong.  There was no tomato in my omelet and they gave me potatoes but no fruit.  When it was time to settle up the check, I asked for the fruit to go and they noticed their error.  They apologized profusely and said there was a new guy working the kitchen.  I never did mention the tomato omission--I was just hungry and didn't want to wait for a new omelet to be made up.  Refills on my soda came quickly and I loved how they offered to split the bill any way we wanted.   I don't get that a horror movie was playing at 11am...maybe that's just their thing.  OK food. Friendly service.

Can you say hole in the wall glory!!  This place being a breakfast joint was a must try for us being in the west loop.  Going in we thought wow this is can't be that good of a place. Yelp wasn't lying this place was great.  The staff was super friendly and the food was well above the norm.  I think being a breakfast/lunch venue has allowed them to get the market they were trying for.  They make the menu easy to pick what you want.  If you are looking for a good ol home cooked meal I highly suggest this place. It's the place for townies not a tourist stop, so they can stick to the basics we love.  If you live in Chicago I highly suggest you stop in and have a meal. I will bet you will be back in, unless you are a yelper and have to try lots of new places. Hope you get the same enjoyment my wife and I did!!
Great spot with no pretension and no lines, have enjoyed breakfast here many times and may do so again today. You really can't go wrong here.
This place cooks everything from all day breakfast to lunch time gyros awesome spot great tasting food can't go wrong with the variety
So tasty; Breakfast is amazing and they're quick on their feet.  It's got an classic Chicago Diner feel.  Eat here! Yummm!!

This place is the best! Your standard old school Chicago Diner that is hard to come by in the West Loop nowadays. I come here every Saturday Morning for breakfasts/brunch and every time I walk-in servers greet me with a smile and already know my order. Give it a shot if you are wanting a great traditional breakfast at the cheapest prices I have seen in the city.

The only thing that beats the food at this place is the people who work there! Everyone is incredibly friendly. I got a HUGE, I mean HUGE and delicious breakfast and coffee for $10. A bunch of construction workers and cops hang out there in the morning during the week, and there was an incredibly friendly, joking feeling throughout the place. I have some dietary restrictions, and they agreed to make some adjustments to the typical food for me no problem. 5 stars! I will definitely be back for more delicious breakfasts!

This is my first ever review on Yelp because honestly? I freaking love this place. It doesn't make sense that this insanely inexpensive gem is nestled 3 blocks from my house in the west loop. It also doesn't make sense that i just walked in on a Saturday and immediately got a table. The food here is no frills: eggs, omelettes, skillets, burgers, bacon, sausage, pancakes. I've only had breakfast here but it's all delicious. You aren't gonna get weird creations here, just delicious straightforward diner food served by great waitresses. I can't say enough good things. Can't imagine waiting 45 minutes for one of the hot spot places to spend triple on things that don't taste as good.

We came here for breakfast and were seated right away as we might have been the 4th table filled. It was disappointing that it took so long for our food to come out, and my boyfriend's mom and boyfriend's order got partially mixed up. I got an omelette with hashbrowns on the side. It was just ok. I like my hashbrowns more crispy and they were definitely more on the softer side. The place is like a diner and so they get their regulars and it made me wonder if and what was causing other tables to get their food out first or before us. The prices are reasonable and the service was ok. Between waiting a while for someone to take our order, and then adding on to that the time we actually got it I doubt we'd come back.
When I want breakfast this is the place I come !!! Parking is always available the waiters (Kim) are always fast and on point they make me feel like I'm at home I love this place
Always a friendly atmosphere and the waitresses are always on top of it. Great food  ! Thanks on behalf of David !!!

The four star rating this restaurant had posted is about as trustworthy as beauty school haircut. The menu which was covered in whiteout and created by a middle school student had more food on it than what came out on my plate.  Not only did they forget my food but when it came out it looked as though one of the rats in the kitchen dined on it first.  You should totally eat here if you want to have diarrhea.

Man, I love this place.  A few coworkers and I started going here a few months back, and now it's (at least) a weekly affair. Killer lunch options, but I almost exclusively opt for the stellar eggs. The skillets rule, as do the omelettes. Coffee overfloweth, thanks to the attentive (and very friendly!) waitstaff. This place has all the charm that a classic Chicago diner should, with awesome food to boot.  I'm so happy to be a regular here!

A friend and I stopped by this little diner for a late lunch one day. We came in an hour before closing, but the staff were very patient and delivered exceptional service. The food served here is exceptional for a very reasonable (on the cheaper end even) price. I ordered a breakfast plate with eggs, ham, and hashbrown and toast, my friend got the Caesar salad with grilled chicken. Both portions were huge! The owner even held a casual, friendly conversation with us. Overall, this place is a little gem in this neighborhood full of upscale bars and dining.
First time here.  Had a bacon omelet.   Service and food was fine.  Prices could be slightly lower.

Greasy spoon hiding in plain sight?  We'll take it.  Fits the neighborhood well and will become a go-to especially if I try to go to Au Cheval and there's a huge wait.  Pancakes and french toast were great and I blew it by not trying the hash browns.  The shake wasn't legendary but you get a lot of it for just a few bucks.  The definition of cop joint--eight cops came in during my 45-minute visit this past weekend during brunchtime on a Sunday.
Breakfast or lunch I've gone for years and never have had a problem. Friendly staff ,good prices and the best is the free parking!

We came on a Saturday morning around 9 (and I had a 10 am appointment in the neighborhood), the place was busy not packed.  A waffle and an omelet took 45 mins to be delivered to our table (after following up at 30th minute). 3 (6 people) other tables had been served (by the other waiter 1 of just 2), despite ordering way after us, and bills already paid before our food arrived.  At first, it was the waffle maker not functioning, we could've been notified and order replaced... but not even a check-up visit regarding food (coffee was constantly refilled though, thank you).  Then we were told that there was a large order that came in that morning and they were short-handed.     Food wasn't bad at all, it was just bad timing.  We got some discount on our food and the cashier did offer up a free meal for next visit. Unfortunately, the experience left a bitter taste.

So after 10 years of visiting the snack shop, I think we must part ways.. Waiting more than half hour-40 minutes for our meal is just ridiculous..I can wait that long for a pizza L, but not for a chicken pita that doesn't even have Greek dressing nor Caesar dressing in my husbands order.. People are leaving because of the poor service.. Miss the old owners and the speediness, good flavor, and reasonable prices.. The prices are higher $1-2 & the service is poor and the chicken was flavorless along w the free flan they gave everyone to try.. Sorry but this is not good.

I've been here a few times for lunch with my coworkers and, over time, our opinion on Johnnie's has only gotten worse. First, let's start with the recent price increase on EVERYTHING on the menu. Someone actually brushed white out on all the prices and increased each by at least $1... And while we're on the subject of poor pricing, I ordered a burger special which was priced at $7.79 on their "specials" menu. When the check came it was $9.99... this must be some sort of mistake, right? Well, no, apparently not. They expected me to realize that the double ended "arrow" they drew on the menu was there to tell me that the price was swapped with another burger that was $9.99. MY BAD. It wasn't even worth arguing because the staff is so impatient and rude. If I wasn't with my coworkers they would have heard a mouthful, but we were on company time so I it held back. I guess now is a good time to mention that I had to wait for the cashier/waitress to duck back into the kitchen to take a drag from her cigarette before ringing me up. Health violation anyone? As for service, it's slow and the waitresses are extremely forgetful. I've heard coworkers complain enough times to know this for a fact. In my most recent visit the waitress didn't even try to remember who ordered what, and at least 3 items were forgotten at various points during our meal. Expect to get your order screwed up and sassed for bringing it up.

I swung into Johnnie's Snack Shop for lunch on a Saturday and was pleasantly surprised. Décor: It's a pretty basic place (not a bad thing) when the order counter right when you walk in and a bunch of tables leading into the rear. It's well lit, (semi) clean, and pretty inviting. Basically you order at the counter and leave (if you're taking to go) or grab a seat. That's it, but that's what I'm a fan of! Simple! Bathroom: unknown Staff: The cashier and the waitress were very friendly and nice and my food was prepared quickly. Food: I had the Turkey Club sandwich and a drink (one size fits all). The sandwich was solid, well made, and tasty. Value: I ended up spending a bit more than I thought for just a sandwich and a drink... I'd like to see the prices come down a bit. I'm a fan of this little spot and would like to come back and try out their breakfast sometime soon.
Cozy little diner setting, I come here for breakfast every morning. The people are really great and make you feel at home. The food is good and the prices are fair. Would recommend to other!

Friend and I tried to go to Little Goat but there was an hour wait so we decided to just get a quick bite here and we were far from disappointed. Really cheap, really good, classic diner food. I ordered the Deuces Wild which came with 2 pancakes or french toast, 2 Eggs and 2 bacon or sausage. Plenty of food, almost hard to finish it all.

The one star is for the bad customer service from the short/chunky girl on register. I had to wait until she finished her conversation before she took my order. She huffs and puffs and rolls her eyes cuz I'm not quick my order.  I won't be going back.
Great local diner with fantastic food, friendly staff, and big portions.  The greek omellete with potatoes and toast is under $8.  Now they have free parking too!
Great diner and awesome prices! The chili is everything and I love the breakfast sandwiches!

we stopped for breakfast on Oct 25th. Breakfast was rally good! service was outstanding and the prices were very reasonable. I had sausage eggs and hash browns, my wife had an omelet and they gave us a large portion and tasted great. when we come back again we definitely plan on stopping back and trying luch out also.
I love this place!   Been coming here for over 3 years now and hands down the best service!  Charlene is amazing, great food, great service, great coffee...early mornings are perfect!  :)
Good food, good for locals. One of the few moderately priced joints in the neighborhood. Usually go for breakfast, but have lunch there as well.
Very clean and light food. Perfect portions and at a wallet friendly price. And a great service to top that!

Don't be fooled by the nondescript storefront, this place is super comfortable and clean. Unlike other all- day breakfast diners, this place makes their food nice and light without a ton of oil and fat yet still flavorful. The service is excellent as well.

Had lunch 2 days in a row.  Work related visit.  Both days food was prepared excellent , eye appealing and served with plenty of personality  Hope To get back again to this restaurant.   Recommend this restaurant
I always come in for breakfast or lunch if I'm in the neighborhood. Always fast, super friendly service.  The food has always been great. I will continue to come back!

What a great diner.  They KEEP IT SIMPLE, STUPID!  I don't like pancakes, because everyone messes with the original recipe.  Our waitress was awesome, and the staff was nice too.  I will be back, many many many times.  I really should just stay here all day and eat.

I have been a loyal customer for several months. Changes have taken place since ownership has changed. I ordered earlier this week  a grilled cheese sandwich , soup and a beverage, and was told that they could not deliver under $10.00. the order totaled $9.83.  I asked would you sacrifice $9.83 for .017 cents? I was asked if I want the order it would have to be $10.00. The waitress was abrupt. I added to the order and 55 minutes later my grilled cheese arrived, cold, moist bread and maybe 1 piece of cheese, soup was cold, the only thing semi hot was the pizza puff. That I was able to eat, thither other food went to the garbage.  Today I though okay one more chance.  I placed my order grilled pork chops, with grilled veggies, and tomato soup. $12.54. I was told that they were busy and could I wait 45 minutes for the order, I told her not a problem since that appears to be how long its been the last few weeks anyway. Order was placed at 1:06pm, I get a call from the driver at 2:10pm that he was lost but was coming now. He arrived at 2:15pm, food bag turned over sideway, food and liquid dripping all over. Paid the bill, I opened the bag, everything was soaking wet from condensation, the veggies, were saturated, the pork chops hard and the soup had congealed.   I called to speak to the new owner Shati, not there, I was given a Manager, who asked me point blank not even hearing the complaint. I told her I wanted my money back, she said she would but I would have to return the food. I told here I threw the food out because it was soaking wet and she told me that she was sorry but could not do a refund.  I would think that's what she would have done with it when it would come back to the restaurant. So if she is throwing the food out I should get my money back.  I questioned that, I was told look I am only the manager, blah blah blah.  I loved this place, it was reasonable , friendly food came on time, hot and was pretty good.  Now that it has been taken over, the cook has quit, the staff is rude, and the food takes forever to get here.   Shati-message to the wise, maybe you wont see the difference on your bottom line because I will not order any longer, but you will eventually see it down the line, because people will not accept this type of service. Just so you know I ordered at least 4 days a week, maybe twice a day, so my weekly $60.00 for the past several months may not hurt your pocket, but if you get two or three more like me you will see the difference.

The name is kind of misleading. Its definitely a diner with lots of breakfast options. big portions. sandwich with a diet coke, a boatload of crispy fries, and soup (homemade and actually pretty good even though I dont usually like soup), for $7.76 including tax!

While in Chicago for the weekend I ate here twice, which is a testament to how exceptional the service & food was!  I first tried going around the corner to another restaurant, but after seeing that the place was crawling with hipsters and had a 1.5 hour wait I was out.  I quickly consulted yelp for another highly rated joint, but without hundreds of reviews - as I quickly realized, the sheep like their herds :)  Johnny's was just the ticket, as there was no wait whatsoever and the waitress was immediately attentive to us!  Both times there I was quite impressed with how much time/attention we were given, most waitresses seem to be reading off a script and rush taking your order - not here, they make sure it's right!  I was aware they paid attention to detail when I saw glass bottles of ketchup- they realize that even the best fries won't taste perfect without the freshness and full bodied flavor of ketchup from a glass bottle!  The food was much better quality than I would ever have expected from a diner-esque restaurant - juicy, flavor packed sandwiches on both occasions!
Been here 3 times for breakfast. Friendly service, good food and reasonable prices. If you're looking for an unpretentious place for breakfast, this is it.

Johnny's the place to sit back and enjoy a great meal, one of my favorite places to start off the day with amazing coffee friendly service and outstanding waffles and omelet's.  The décor is even cooler with great seating and free parking!  Looking forward to next time!

I love this place! It  reminds me of the diners I would go to for breakfast when I lived on the Northwest side.  The food is great the portions are very generous the staff is SO nice, I'd like to give them five HUNDRED stars as opposed to merely five....... I really hope they remain here for a long time.
Best pancakes in town! We have been coming to this hidden gem for years. Lots of new additions lately including wifi and parking.
We love this food! It's so delicious and hot! The delivery is quick and the owner, Michael, is very pleasant and nice! We will be eating from here a lot! :)
I love this place. This my go-to breakfast joint when I'm visiting Chicago. Great service. Great atmosphere and you can't beat their prices.

Johnny's is great for your standard breakfast: delicious omelets, skillets, french toast and coffee. very reasonable prices. the service is good and the place is nice and clean. will have to try their lunch next time.  they also have a parking lot which is unheard of in this area. easy in and out! BONUS: they have a magic show on Sundays! very entertaining even for adults.

I would give Johnny's Snack shop 4.5 stars. I would probably have never come here if I didn't live down the street from here, but I'm glad I do. I know this is a trek for some people who don't live in west loop. It has an old fashioned diner feel to it and I always walk in and get to pick where I sit. The waitresses always bring a cup of coffee and fill it almost immediately.  The portions are large and breakfast at a very reasonable price. I usually always get the 3-3-3 (3 of a kind) with 3 chocolate chip pancakes, bacon and over easy eggs. There is always more than enough food and all this with a coffee is $10 out the door! There are always a few Chicago policeman in here so you know it is a great diner. Just a helpful tip: The first time I came here I didn't know you had to take your check up to the register yourself.  Overall a great diner that is exactly what you need for some breakfast after a long night or in general.

Great diner food, and very friendly staff and owners   I have only had their breakfast, which is you typical diner food, but is very good and extremely well priced for Chicago   They deliver!   One of my favorite and few places that will deliver breakfast quickly and very friendly
The food was amazing and the people who worked at the restaurant  were very very nice. I felt like I was at home. I would come back!!

This is definitely the place to go when you are ready to eat good food with that home cooked taste.  The service is friendly and the prices are reasonable considering that they are located near the downtown area. Love the 2-2-2. Pancakes and coffee are always on point!

A coworker of mine usually ordered from Johnny's whenever she was in the office, and since my favorite restaurant has been closed for a while now, I decided to try Johnny's out. I have eaten several things off of their menu and the food is fantastic! Good and filling, and it never hurts the wallet!! The staff is super friendly whenever I walk in, and delivery is awesomely fast! Haven't been disappointed with anything on their menu yet, and I'm a very picky eater! I definitely recommend it.
This place is a huge surprise! Pretty cool old style looking, amazing food and very friendly environment! So Glad I walked by and decided to try it

Great for breakfast or lunch. A small family-run diner that serves up warm food quickly. Great service and friendly employees, this is my go-to breakfast joint because the food is good and the prices can't be beat.

Get the pork chops and eggs...you won't be disappointed. Other favorites include oat meal, BLT, and pepper and egg sandwich.   I've been coming here basically my entire life, so what can I really say--it's like reviewing your best friend.  If you're looking for a trendy place with organic ingredients, etc., then proceed to one of the many such places around the corner.  But if you're looking for a down to earth place with great food, great prices, and an A+ staff, come to Johnnie's! And if I wasn't clear on this, GET THE PORK CHOPS AND EGGS!
So good after a night of drinking!  I had the corn-beef omelette and hashbrowns, it was really good.  Fast and friendly service and great food!

What a great spot.  Where else can you get a giant sandwich, mountain of fries and a soup for $8?  Breakfast is also very good.  Overall, I have started going to Johnny's about once per week for lunch for carry-out.  Dining there is also very good, service is good, very prompt.  Overall, a really good spot.

I have been driving and walking by here for the last 4 years and this weekend my husband and I finally decided to try it.  I am glad we did.   When you walk in it is much cleaner than you expect from a old school diner.  Service was good, people were friendly.  You get a ton of food for the price.  Its at least $2-3 less per entree than most others around.   We had the Greek omelet and the Gyro Omelet.  Both were very good although I think the gyro was a little better.  great flavor and was not greasy.  We both got hashbrowns with our meals which were fine.  I personally prefer mine a little more crunchy so maybe next time we would ask them for well done instead but we will definitely be back.  Cash Only

It wasn't bad... No. I take that back. It was pretty bad. My friend asked me if I would ever return to Johnny's Snack Shop and my answer was ready and on the table: NO. I explained: there are plenty of better cheap restaurants close to where I live and there is no reason for me to make a trek to Johnny's Snack Shop. If I lived on the same block and needed a quick, cheap meal then sure thing. I'd go back; however, that reality doesn't exist for me. Our only reason for going to Johnny's Snack Shop was that my friend didn't want to wait an hour for The Little Goat around the corner. IMHO, we should have waited that freakin' hour. My Tuna Caesar Salad cost $7.50, but I would have rather paid $15 for something that I couldn't have made myself. All of my homemade breakfasts out-shined Johnny's Snack Shop. Sure. We got a table right away. But there were folks sitting a few tables over who (obviously) were dressed in clubbing clothes (defined as glittery, slinky tops, leather mini-skirts, and thigh-highs) and smeared make-up on their youthful faces who had partied the night through and were going strong into the morning. Next to them were two or three tables of cops. It was a very different scene from the yuppies at my destination of choice. This is what we ordered: my aforementioned salad, cinnamon raisin French Toast, and some sort of skillet. I think that ALL of this food was perceived and appreciated as bodily sustenance to quiet ravenous hunger and not as a pleasant edible experience. I mean, my salad was made with iceberg lettuce and had ice-cream scoops of tuna salad on top. The two or three tomato wedges tasted funny. I can't really comment on the skillet except that I easily skipped over it on the menu and then felt validated when I saw it. The French Toast was made with cinnamon raisin bread that you get from Jewel: thin and small. It did not come with anything except for a few triangles of French Toast on a plate. Even my non-foodie companions commented that a visual once-over deemed those triangles lacking. Service was alright. It was quick and polite but rustic. Like, there was no charm or nuance that is found in surrounding restaurants. They brought us our check and we sat for one or two conversation topics waiting for them to take our money only to realize that we needed to pay at the counter. Nobody told us about that. My friends live over an hour-drive away from here. I wish they could have conquered their need for instant gratification so that they could enjoy an even more satisfying meal. Our only purpose for going to Johnny's Snack Shop was for a quick fix and it was just that. So two stars for not having a wait and serving us edible (but not delicious) food.
Love Johnny's...just a good old fashioned diner.  You know its good when all the cops hang out in there!
Great pancakes and ham is never salty.  Owners are great and remember all their customers.

Love this place. Service is great. Nice ladies who always make me feel at home. Food is  good & very cheap! Not fancy at all but cool photos to look at. Love the charlie chaplin & pit picture. Now only if they had a outdoor patio it would be amazing.
Great lunchs and breakfasts. Quick delivery too for a minimal charge. Order multiple times per week.  Excellent cream of chicken rice soup.

I would give this place a 3.5 stars for the food but I feel like rounding up because the staff was really nice.  It's very cheap and their portions are large. However, the omelet I got was just okay. The pancakes were fluffy.  It place has an old timey dinner feel and people were super nice.

I recently started working in the West Loop and went here for lunch with coworkers (they are regulars).  What a pleasant surprise.  Nice place and large portions of great tasting food for very low prices.  You can get a huge sandwich, fries or Greek potatoes and a cup of soup for $5.00 plus tax.  Or select from their delicious breakfast items. Very pleasant and efficient wait staff too.  Totally satisfied.  I will be back again and again and again!

After reading about it here on Yelp, and craving a good vacation breakfast for almost a week, I made it to Johnny's Snack Shop on a last -second change of plans.  We had originally planned to hit a newer place around the corner, but I just wanted a decent traditional breakfast in a small place where the locals go instead of some foo-foo trendy kind of food, so I walked back to Johnny's.  I was not disappointed.  If I lived in Chicago, I would go back at least one day each week for breakfast.  This clean, unpretentious, old school diner served me a hearty breakfast that lasted me well into the afternoon of a long day of air travel back home.  I had the Cubed Steak and eggs with small pancakes and was nearly not able to clean my plates, and I like to eat.  A generous helping of potatoes which were perfectly cooked, a half-pound patty of ordinary cubed steak, and three intact OE eggs came along with a couple of delicious buttermilk pancakes and hot maple syrup.  A bottomless cup of coffee was never allowed to get below half full.  Mind you, it was not busy at all during our visit, so we had the staff's full attention and we waited ten minutes max for our food.  Our server was cheerful and each person working at Johnny's greeted us with a hearty and genuine "Good Morning" as if we were regulars.  The decor of old Chicago photos gave me a sense of local flavor that I had been looking for in a place while on vacation.  A hearty breakfast for two came to under $20 with tip.  The next time I am in Chicago, I know where I will be going for breakfast.  This place does it right.

I love this place. It's very... quaint. It's the kind of place that you feel good frequenting. The staff is friendly and greets you with a smile as you walk in. It definitely feels like a throwback diner, but I think it just hasn't evolved as quickly as the west loop neighborhood it's in. The prices are probably among the best in town, and the portions are very fair. I never regret stopping in here for a bite to eat, and I always feel safe because at any given time there's a table of police officers enjoying a meal. Always a good sign.

Johnnies is an outstanding diner experience. Inexpensive, great diner food and a bottomless cup a joe. The owner and waitress are outstandingly attentive and extremely kind and accommodating.   You're almost guaranteed to see some of Chicago's finest munching on a fat sando during their break. Go here for the food, stay for the charm.

I was nervous at first given the curb appeal; however, went there on a Sunday morning for breakfast.  While I do like all of the new and fancy brunch spots, Johnny's is an old school diner that serves old school/traditional breakfasts.  While you shouldn't expect anything fancy, you can expect good/traditional food and a great place to have a relaxing breakfast.

You walk by and think it's going to be short-order to-go. Not so fast! Classic Greek diner food...good omelets and hash browns, though the grits could probably use cheese.  Big cheery room, friendly wait staff.

Recently stumbled upon this place and love every moment of it. Huge portions so make sure you come hungry. Ham off the bone is great, and I don't believe its on the menu but you can get Italian bread with breakfast which comes slathered in butter.  You can come here spend $10 on breakfast, skip lunch, and still have to talk yourself into dinner. They now accept credit cards too!

The 23 reviews was right, this is a 4 star place.  This hole in the wall, no frills, dive, diner has great breakfast.  Their prices are cheap and the portions are good.  I haven't been there for lunch or dinner yet, but that would be my next visit.  I'm not going to Yolk or Brunch after visiting this place.  Many pictures of old Chicago line up the walls of the place.  They raised prices again, but still a good buy.

I really wanted to love this place. It's off the beaten path, seemingly populated by regulars, has uber-friendly service and has the gritty feel of a real urban diner. Yet, I didn't love it... at least on my first trip. My honest rating would be 3.5 stars, but I rounded up because the employees were so nice. I ordered a cubed steak and eggs (over medium). It was accompanied by some respectable breakfast potatoes, but the steak tasted more of seasoning than beef and the eggs, while cooked properly, were tasteless. My OJ was large (maybe 16-18oz), and was even offered to be refilled. The online menu that I scrounged up was dated, and the prices listed were perhaps $2 under what I experienced on-site. I'd say it is priced appropriately for diner food at that location, but it is not worth going out of your way to score a bargain. I think I'll come back for lunch next time. It's close enough to the loop to be walkable if you've got a little time on your hands, and I really want them to succeed. The staff are worth rooting for.

The only thing I don't like is on their specials they don't list the price. The lady running the cashier gave me a dirty look when I asked -  like I was a jerk off because I wanted to know a price. Other than that they have great prices for the West Loop area.

This is probably one of the nicest diners I have ever been to. The inside is really quaint and clean. The service is super friendly, you feel like you're family. They have a nice menu full of feel good eats and breakfast foods. Everything tasted great, wasn't really greasy, and came speedy fast. And it's cheap!

Hell ya - for a good, not greasy, relatively inexpensive breakfast in the West Loop, this is a good bet - skip Lou Michell's for this place, for sure - clean surroundings, attentive staff - food brought out quickly, properly prepared

Perfect little neighborhood greek breakfast/lunch joint. Been here a few times and I will be going back. They are not reinventing the wheel at all but they are doing what they are supposed to be doing the old fashioned way. Sometimes it's nice to just have a normal cheeseburger or eggs and bacon without a twist. The deliver and their prices are reasonable. (and the soups are good too!)

Very solid.  Good diner/fast food at a very reasonable price, which is often hard to find in the West Loop.  I get a kick out of the pictures from their former location.  Also, get a load of the prices they were charging mentioned in the Tribune article on the wall when they closed the former location.  I've had breakfast dishes here a couple of times, plus a variety of the other.  At lunch, I often get one of their dinners and part for dinner or lunch the next day.  What can I say, I love a bargain and I'm trying to lose weight!

Cops and breakfast. That's how I'd describe this little joint in the West Loop. I will usually come here for breakfast and it's usually the sandwich. But I have eaten in with a full omelette, which is a great deal. What is remarkable about Johnny's is the artwork, photos from an old newspaper. They offer (me) an endless source of amusement. That and the ATM which has a very prominent location near the front door -- because their cash only. Considering the options on this corner, this is the place to go for what the others lack and at an affordable price.

Every time I eat here which is at least once a month the food is delicious.  The prices are great.  I get the Johnny's special which is 2 eggs, 2 pancakes/french toast and 2 pieces of meat for $4.95.  Most of the time I can barely finish my plate.  The pancakes have to be the best in the city.  My wife usually gets a chicken breast sandwich that comes with two breasts, freshly made chicken noodle soup and a roll, plus fries for $8.  It's a family run business which I want to support.  From the outside, it may not look promising but you'll be blown away by how great the food is and how nice the staff is. One other note: they do take credit cards and have for a couple of years as I have used them there for a couple of years.  I was there again on 12/31/11 and paid with my credit card.

I passed this place up a thousand times on my way to Greek time. I finally stopped in after hearing about how great there omelletes were. Ahe was so right it was great. The staff was all very nice. My server was very sweet. Johhny's is a hidden gem.

Might not look ilke much from the outside but the inside is SPOTLESS!! Looks like maybe new owners or something? Anyway, Standard Grill Menu with a few kickers--"Chicken Mozz Omelettes"/"Rib Eye Sandwich"/"Pita Sandwiches"/etc.... Definitely Greek Diner type of menu! The food is great and comes out very quickly. They have a couple servers and everything you need (Condiments/Hot Sauce/Etc) is right on the table which is perfect... Lots of Cops in here if that tells you anything!? Plus they serve Breakfast ALL DAY and Have FREE Delivery... GTFJD!

$2.90 for a huge freshly cooked hot dog with a mountain of yummy french fries... Need I say more? They serve breakfast all day, the prices are super cheap for the quality of the food they serve. My new favorite place for lunch.  Not to mention the decor and seating area are too cute... Don't be fooled by the outside appearance.

I loved this place. Had driven by several times and it never really looked open. Looks different from the outside than it is on the inside. Clean and spiffy inside. Lovely servers and the food was QUICK to come out after we ordered. I thoroughly enjoyed my omlette and potatoes. MmmMmmM! I ordered the Denver but subbed bacon for ham. Excellent! Great diner feel. A hidden gem fo' sho!

I don't know how this place was before, but from the looks of the pics its safe to say they classed up the place alot! Don't be fooled by the extrerior, the inside of this place reminds me of pure old schoiol Chicago, with some great classic pics on the wall. Its very clean and well lit, plus has that cozy diner feel to it, complete with the cooks and giant grill in the front. For the record I love it when diners offer you coffee and give you free refills. PLUS I drink lots of water, and i love it when they just leave you a giant picture of jar or whatever...but thats just me. If you like giant drinks it seems thgis place follows the Mike K motto of only serving giant glasses, as it seems there soft drinks only come in huge glasses built for one serving. THIS IS A GOOD THING FOR YOU! Oh yeah, the food...nothing super special, typical diner food, great reasonable prices...the create your own omlette deal is kick ass! As i think of it...damn that omlette was frickin good! This is definitely one of the best diners I've been to...the servers are nice and friendly, unlike other places where you'd swear you were late with your rent and the servers were the cranky landlord.

I walked by a million times but from the outside it looked to dingy to venture inside.  There aren't many options around here for breakfast on Saturday so it was time to explore.  We opened the door and... what the hell?  It looks great.  The walls were brightly painted yellow with nicely framed black and white pictures and a brand new ceiling with some mock tin tiles.  Uhh... someone post a real picture here on Yelp because this was a suprise.  Cops, regular and SWAT time abound.  A patrol vehicle always seems to be parked outside.  If anything, I feel safe from other people... at least it's not a bar or I'd be afraid of the cops, see the incidents at Jefferson Tap etc.   At any rate, the Gyros omlette was massive, great and inexpensive!  It was fairly quiet compared to the usual Chicago breakfast ruckus everywhere else.  The waitress was sweet as well.  This will hit the breakfast rotation.

Johnny's is as good as it gets when it comes to diners.  I go about once a week with some guys from my office and there is a reason we keep coming back; good breakfast, friendly staff, fast service, and very affordable.  As of no more than a month ago they totally renovated the place and it looks great and they managed to not increase their prices.  They are also now accepting credit cards (they used to be cash only).  I would recommend Johnny's to anyone who wants to grab a quick breakfast without any frills just good eats and nice people.   Thanks Johnny's keep up the good work.

What a find!  They have outstanding greasy spoon food and exceptional prices.  I carried out, but the servers were extremely friendly and the food was ready in no time.  The breakfast menu looked amazing!  I'll be coming back here to sample other menu items.
Mmm... good, cheap diner right by my house.  I will definitely come back here for breakfast again and again.

Johnny's snack shop is what every other diner in the world should aspire to be. Hear that Clark's? Take some notes.  It's cheap, hot, delicious food in vinyl booths. Fountain pop in big plastic glasses, with refills. The menu is uncomplicated, yet chocked full of greasy spoon delights. The waitress that took care of us was all smiles, and unlike Clark's...ahem...didn't look like she wanted to poke our eyes out with a fork. Cheers to that! The guys up at the grill are chattering away, and even the cashier was sweet as pie...ohhh. pie. Yeah that looked good, too.  3 people, $20...and very stuffed.  My only beef (speaking of, the Italian Beef is HUGE) is that it's cash only. However, they do have an ATM inside...so no biggie.

Quickly becoming one of my favorite diners of all time, and my regular Saturday breakfast stop. I have been here many times, and everything I've had has been great and they treat you like family. There only about a dozen tables so you might have a brief wait while you smell the delicious food on the grill. The three 2's breakfast is my favorite -- with 2 eggs, bacon or sausage, french toast or pancakes and a small OJ for only $3.50. The burgers are top notch as well. Stop by if you are hanging out in Greektown or on the way to UIC... just head over early as they close by 3.

When you walk up, i know what your thinking... "is this the place?"  and the answer is "Yep!"  It's not the best looking establishment I have ever dined in but if you are in a rush get in there.  All there breakfast food is the same as anywhere else but the Greek chicken salad, without onions, is the awesome.  I have never had a salad fill me up like this.  Well... this is my first review, do people review your reviews?  Alright yelpers!  See ya  around!!!
decent hot dogs, they have all the fixins and they are cheap and fast.  they only take cash though so prepared
